sentences: Stu Phillips (born January 19, 1933) is a Canadian-American country singer from Montreal, Quebec.
Stu and his wife Aldona operate Long Hollow Winery in Goodlettsville, near Nashville.
Phillips was inducted into the Canadian Country Music Hall of Fame in 1993.
He was ranked #29 in RPM Magazine's top 57 Canadian Country artists from 1964 to 1994.
